<item>
            <title>[SEC-2550] Classloader leak in Java 7 and 8 but not 6</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2550</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have an integration test in my application that tests for classloader leaks and it fails since I introduced spring security. Therefore I tried reproducing the problem with the helloworld-jc sample and it also leaks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;package the helloworld-jc application&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;start a tomcat with java 7 or 8&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;deploy the application&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;stop the application&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;execute &apos;Find Leaks&apos;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;see that the application leaks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If you start the application with Java 6, everything works. Therefore this might actually be a java problem but I don&apos;t know where to report such a problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also took a heap dump and looked for GC roots from the webappclassloader but could not find any.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Tomcat 7.0.52&lt;br/&gt;
Java 1.6.0_45&lt;br/&gt;
Java 1.7.0_51&lt;br/&gt;
Java 1.8.0&lt;br/&gt;
Windows Server 2008 R2</environment>
